From: Hannes Reinecke <hare@kernel.org>
Date: Wed, 28 May 2025 08:45:33 +0200
Subject: nvme-tcp: sanitize request list handling
Patch-mainline: v6.16-rc1
Git-commit: 0bf04c874fcb1ae46a863034296e4b33d8fbd66c
References: CVE-2025-38264 bsc#1246387

Validate the request in nvme_tcp_handle_r2t() to ensure it's not part of
any list, otherwise a malicious R2T PDU might inject a loop in request
list processing.

Signed-off-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@kernel.org>
Reviewed-by: Sagi Grimberg <sagi@grimberg.me>
Signed-off-by: Christoph Hellwig <hch@lst.de>
[dwagner: drop the lentry handling, downstream is missing this part]
Acked-by: Daniel Wagner <dwagner@suse.de>
---
 drivers/nvme/host/tcp.c |    9 ++++++++-
 1 file changed, 8 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/nvme/host/tcp.c
+++ b/drivers/nvme/host/tcp.c
@@ -280,7 +280,7 @@ nvme_tcp_fetch_request(struct nvme_tcp_q
 	req = list_first_entry_or_null(&queue->send_list,
 			struct nvme_tcp_request, entry);
 	if (req)
-		list_del(&req->entry);
+		list_del_init(&req->entry);
 	spin_unlock(&queue->lock);
 
 	return req;
@@ -575,6 +575,13 @@ static int nvme_tcp_handle_r2t(struct nv
 	}
 	req = blk_mq_rq_to_pdu(rq);
 
+	if (!list_empty(&req->entry)) {
+		dev_err(queue->ctrl->ctrl.device,
+			"req %d unexpected r2t while processing request\n",
+			rq->tag);
+		return -EPROTO;
+	}
+
 	ret = nvme_tcp_setup_h2c_data_pdu(req, pdu);
 	if (unlikely(ret))
 		return ret;
